How to Build GWT application
------------------------

Prerequisites:

1. JDK >= 1.5

2. Apache Ant >= 1.7.0

3. Apache Tomcat >= 7.0

4. GWT SDK >= 2.3.0


1. Change 'local.properties' file containing gwt.sdk && junit.jar definitions:
	gwt.sdk=<path to the GWT SDK folder>
	junit.jar=<path to the junit jar>
E.g., on my computer 'local.properties' consists of 2 lines:
	gwt.sdk=/home/bac1ca/programming/gwt-2.3.0
	junit.jar=/home/bac1ca/downloads/junit-4.9b3.jar

2. To build, just run 'ant build'.

3. To deploy, just run 'ant deploy'.

4. To testing, just run 'ant test'.

5. To creating eclipse project, just run 'ant eclipse.generate'.

